title: Independent Candidate Khawaja Salah Ud Din Akbar wins PP-285 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Independent Candidate, Khawaja Salah Ud Din Akbar has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-285, Taunsa-II by securing 31,817 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Sardar Muhammad Akram Khan of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP), who bagged 25,811 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 58.71%.
